tocrats as wife-givers and wife-takers (that is, as in-laws). She concludes by considering various models that explain how societies may develop or define aristocracies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAristocracy (Social class). 0aChiefdoms. 0aFathers-in-law. 0aKinshipxPhilosophy. 0aMothers-in-law. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/73119640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292759787423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292759787/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK